# Hub Workflow Enforcement

- In this workspace, Appdoers Hub is the source of truth for work tracking.
- Before changing code, ensure a Hub ticket exists for the request.
- If no ticket is provided, create one in stage `pm` and share the ticket id.
- On implementation start, move ticket to `developer`.
- Before handing work back, add a progress note and move to `qa` (or `reviewer` if QA already done).
- Never move to `done` unless QA + review are explicitly confirmed.
- Prefer using `node tools/hub-workflow-cli.mjs` for all ticket actions.
- Include ticket id in status updates and final response.
